The paper deals with the study of permutations and their properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DM, cs.CC). The use of adjacencies in computation suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of permutations as a symmetric group also has connections to group theory (cs.GT). Finally, the proposed model for estimating the expected number of moves to sort a permutation suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
